Photo_Mike_16

Copied

I recently discovered Neural filters but never used them. I'm using PS 2022 23.0 release. When I first tried the filters I clicked on the download icon to get access to each one.

 

I soon found just about every tool was visible but all the sliders are greyed out an not accessible. In smart portrait I'm not able to toggle the button to "on" and the sliders are greyed out. In Landscape Mixer I can toggle the button to the right by selecting a filter (picture) but it doesn't turn blue and sliders are greyed out. I've checked Graphics Card compatibility and I have the all clear on every aspect. I tried disabling grahics card but that didn't work.

 

I looked up all kinds of phrases looking for solutions but there are very few. I did do into the file explorer to locate the plugin downloader file (a possible solution I found online) and delete the file and restated but that didn't work. While it did start me fresh in downloading the filters I got the same result. I also uninstalled PS v23 and reinstalled and that didn't work. 

 

I use PS pretty often and have no problems with other filters, plugins or extensions. See screenshots.
